				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In not math-related music, it seems that C is a reference note. All white keys on a piano can be played starting at C to one octave above that C to play the C major scale. Though I believe that A is the mathematical start of an octave, as it's 440 KHz exactly and almost every audible tone of A is a whole number of KHz, and like you said, it's the letter A, which is the first letter of the alphabet. Pretty much everything after A isn't a whole number of KHz, so I have that reason to believe that A is the real start of an octave.
<br />
<br />EDIT: Also, the piano starts with an A as the bottom key. Just thought I'd mention that.</div>

					
