				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Here's the formula I use:
<br />F = B * 2^((N-N0)/12)
<br />
<br />Where B is some arbitrary base frequency
<br />N is your note number (in half steps, 12 notes to an octave)
<br />N0 is the note number of frequency B
<br />
<br />B=440 and N0=57 by the definition of note A4.
<br />
<br />Note numbers:
<br />Examples of notes include C4, D2, A#3, etc.  It's a note name, optional sharp or flat, and octave number.
<br />Named notes are numbered like this:
<br />C=0
<br />D=2
<br />E=4
<br />F=5
<br />G=7
<br />A=9
<br />B=11
<br />For sharp, add 1.  For flat subtract 1.
<br />
<br />C4 = 12*4 + 0 = #48
<br />D2 = 12*2 + 2 = #26
<br />F#3 = 12*3 + 9 + 1 = #42
<br />A4 = 12*4 + 9 = #57
<br />A4 is defined to have a frequency of 440Hz.
<br />
<br />Middle C is C4, and it has a frequency of
<br />=440 * 2^((48-57)/12)
<br />=440 * 2^(-9/12)
<br />=261.625...
<br />
<br />I have no clue where your formula came from.</div>

